---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="0xDiyor — About">
  <h2 class="section-title">About</h2>

  <div class="about">
    <div class="cmd">fastfetch</div>
    <div class="fetch">
      <pre class="logo" aria-hidden="true"><span class="dm">┌────────────────┐</span>
<span class="dm">│</span>                <span class="dm">│</span>
<span class="dm">│</span>  <span class="xd">~$</span> whoami     <span class="dm">│</span>
<span class="dm">│</span>  diyor         <span class="dm">│</span>
<span class="dm">│</span>  <span class="xd">~$</span> <span class="cursor">▊</span>          <span class="dm">│</span>
<span class="dm">│</span>                <span class="dm">│</span>
<span class="dm">└───────┬┬───────┘</span>
<span class="dm">     ┌──┴┴──┐</span>
<span class="dm"> ────┴──────┴────</span></pre>
      <dl class="kv">
        <div><dt>role</dt><dd>cybersecurity student &middot; IT professional</dd></div>
        <div><dt>edu</dt><dd>CCD A.A.S. &rarr; WGU B.S. (May 2026)</dd></div>
        <div><dt>certs</dt><dd>Security+ &middot; Network+ &middot; NCA-AIIO</dd></div>
        <div><dt>lab</dt><dd>Proxmox &middot; Wazuh &middot; Tailscale</dd></div>
        <div><dt>focus</dt><dd>detection engineering &middot; network defense</dd></div>
        <div class="swatches" aria-hidden="true">
          <i style="background:#0a0a0f"></i><i style="background:#1e1e2e"></i><i
            style="background:#6a6a7a"></i><i style="background:#c8c8d0"></i><i
            style="background:#00b87d"></i><i style="background:#00e5a0"></i>
        </div>
      </dl>
    </div>

    <div class="cmd">cat bio.txt</div>
    <div class="prose">
      <p>
        I got into security the way it actually sticks: building things, breaking them, and
        writing down what went wrong. My homelab is where that happens — a Proxmox box running
        Wazuh, Tailscale, and whatever I'm currently studying, documented writeup by writeup
        on this site.
      </p>
      <p>
        Days are IT support — endpoints, tickets, real users — which teaches more about the
        human side of security than any cert. Nights are the A.A.S. in Cybersecurity at
        Community College of Denver, rolling into WGU's B.S. in Cybersecurity &amp; Information
        Assurance in May 2026. I'm aiming at blue-team work: detection engineering and network
        defense, with enough offensive skills to know what I'm defending against.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="cmd">cat now.txt</div>
    <div class="now">
      <div class="item">writing Wazuh detection rules for the homelab</div>
      <div class="item">Proxmox rebuild series — part 3 in progress</div>
      <span class="stamp">last updated 2026-07-10</span>
    </div>

    <div class="cmd">printenv CONTACT</div>
    <div class="connect">
      <a href="https://github.com/0xDiyor" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">github</a>
      <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/diyor-r/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">linkedin</a>
      <a href="/rss.xml">rss</a>
    </div>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  /* Center the whole session block: size it to its widest line
     (fit-content) so the auto margins split the leftover space evenly.
     Text inside stays left-aligned so it reads like terminal output. */
  .about {
    width: fit-content;
    max-width: 100%;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .cmd {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
    margin: 2rem 0 0.9rem;
  }
  .cmd::before {
    content: '~$ ';
    color: var(--accent-dim);
  }
  .about > .cmd:first-child { margin-top: 0; }

  .fetch {
    display: flex;
    gap: 3rem;
    align-items: center;
  }
  .logo {
    font-family: var(--mono);
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    line-height: 1.3;
    color: var(--accent);
    text-shadow: 0 0 20px rgba(0, 229, 160, 0.22);
    white-space: pre;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .logo .dm { color: var(--accent-dim); }
  .logo .xd { color: var(--text-dim); }
  .logo .cursor { animation: blink 1.2s step-end infinite; }

  .kv {
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    line-height: 2;
  }
  .kv div { display: flex; gap: 0; }
  .kv dt {
    color: var(--accent);
    width: 7ch;
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .kv dt::after { content: ':'; color: var(--text-dim); }
  .kv dd { margin: 0; }
  .swatches { gap: 0.3rem; margin-top: 0.5rem; }
  .swatches i { width: 18px; height: 11px; display: inline-block; }

  .prose {
    font-size: 0.88rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
  }
  .prose p { margin-bottom: 1rem; max-width: 64ch; }

  .now {
    border: 1px solid var(--border);
    background: var(--bg-surface);
    padding: 0.9rem 1.1rem;
    font-size: 0.82rem;
    line-height: 1.9;
    max-width: 64ch;
  }
  .now .item::before {
    content: '▸ ';
    color: var(--accent);
  }
  .now .stamp {
    display: block;
    margin-top: 0.4rem;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    color: var(--text-dim);
  }

  .connect { font-size: 0.85rem; }
  .connect a {
    color: var(--text-dim);
    margin-right: 2.5ch;
    transition: color 0.15s;
  }
  .connect a::before {
    content: '> ';
    color: var(--accent-dim);
    font-weight: 700;
  }
  .connect a:hover { color: var(--accent); }

  @media (max-width: 600px) {
    /* Stacked on mobile: center the CRT logo and the facts card */
    .fetch { flex-direction: column; align-items: center; gap: 1.5rem; }
    .logo { font-size: 0.72rem; }
  }
</style>
